nough around to max it out anyway.<br><br>Bagum <p></p><span class=m><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubagumntagum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bagumntagum</A> at: 10/21/01 12:48:28 pm<br></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>45</b>  </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ufaedaerryverwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faedaer Ryverwalker</A> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Master</span><br> </td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pullers</span><br><span class=m><font color=#778899>Posted: 10/21/01 1:53:10 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <hr size=1> You're absolutely correct about pulling with a snare pull. There are situations, however, where a snare is a bad idea. Take, for example, a ranger in the Great Divide pulling a frost giant. Sometimes these are looong pulls. Snare it, you risk more adds, plus the time for the mob to get to the group is ridiculous. Considering the taunt factor of such a spell, it's a bad idea as well. Makes it really hard for the tank to taunt off once the mob does get to the group. What ranger worth his salt doesn't have arrows? I don't know. It was just a thought. If we ever do a long camp in, say, Western Wastes, where the closest fletching supplies would be in Thurgadin, hammers would work, hehe.<br>The situation may never come up. Just an offer. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Fae <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>77</b>  </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ukelwinnomad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KelwinNomad</A> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Leader</span><br> <BR><img src=http://home.rochester.rr.com/jrvarga/images/smkel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pullers</span><br><span class=m><font color=#778899>Posted: 10/21/01 3:00:01 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <hr size=1> also, snare has a range of 30 - 40 feet...   the arrows I carry now have a range of 150 ft...<br><br>this makes it better for me to make it back to the group before that giant starts hitting me and I can be behind the tank before the giant even gets to the group...<br><br>when I do run out of arrows, I usually cast Flame Lick or Ignite which have a range of 40 - 50 feet...  both bring on the MoB and both can easily have the aggro reversed by a good tank...<br><br>I have used the throwing skill once and even scored a hit...  Kirbee gave me a snoball and I threw it at a griff for 2 points of damage...   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I did notice that one time, that distance must be accurate for throwing short ranged objects.  I got a message about being too close for a ranged object, so I backed up and then got a message about being too far away to use this object...  was a bit of a pain... <p><p><font size="5" color="#006600">Kelwin Jumala</font><br><a href="http://home.rochester.rr.com/jrvarga/" target="_blank">Wood Elf Ranger of the 35th Season</a><br><i>"Rangers: Born with the abilities to handle the necessities of Life."</i></p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>76</b>  </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uvear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vear</A> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <BR><img src=http://personal.mia.bellsouth.net/mia/w/h/wht1986/Vear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pullers</span><br><span class=m><font color=#778899>Posted: 10/21/01 11:24:46 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/febonmoonfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <hr size=1> As a monk, I can say I greatly without doubt throw pulling is better than agro pulling. Yes most throwing items have a short rage 40 - 60, but smithed javalins have a range of 150 or so.  If the pull goes bad, it is nice to have that extra distance if you need to FD split the adds and your FD fails.  MY FD is like 180 and fails about 1 in 15 attemps. You really begin to appreciate that extra time to try and FD again, when the mobs quad you for 125 each attack. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> Posts: <b>19</b>  </span></